exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: multi-env table compact format de-noises cells 1`] = `
"# Manual for: Reviewer and Environment-Specific Evidence Test (v1.0.0)\\n\\n_Test reviewer field and environment-keyed evidence results_\\n\\n## Environments Overview\\n\\n| Environment | Description | Variables | Targets | Approval Required |\\n| ----------- | ----------- | --------- | ------- | ----------------- |\\n| staging | Staging environment | NAMESPACE: \\"staging\\"<br>REPLICAS: 2 |  | No |\\n| production | Production environment | NAMESPACE: \\"production\\"<br>REPLICAS: 5 |  | No |\\n\\n## ✈️ Flight Phase (Main Operations)\\n\\n| Step | staging | production |\\n|------|---------|---------|\\n| [ ] Step 1: Deploy Application ✈️👤<br><em>👤 PIC: ops-team@example.com · 👥 Reviewer: sre-lead@example.com</em><br>📎 <em>Evidence Required: screenshot, command_output</em> | Deploy the application to Kubernetes:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml -n \${NAMESPACE}<br>kubectl scale deployment/app --replicas=\${REPLICAS}<br>\`\`\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC · [ ] Reviewer<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**command_output**: Staging deployment output showing 2 pods<br>\`\`\`bash<br>deployment.apps/app created<br>deployment.apps/app scaled<br>NAME      READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE<br>app-0     1/1     Running   0          10s<br>app-1     1/1     Running   0          10s<br><br>\`\`\` | Deploy the application to Kubernetes:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml -n \${NAMESPACE}<br>kubectl scale deployment/app --replicas=\${REPLICAS}<br>\`\`\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC · [ ] Reviewer<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**screenshot**: Production dashboard showing 5 healthy pods<br>![Evidence](./evidence/prod-dashboard.png)<br><br>**command_output**: Production deployment output showing 5 pods<br>\`\`\`bash<br>deployment.apps/app created<br>deployment.apps/app scaled<br>NAME      READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE<br>app-0     1/1     Running   0          15s<br>app-1     1/1     Running   0          15s<br>app-2     1/1     Running   0          15s<br>app-3     1/1     Running   0          15s<br>app-4     1/1     Running   0          15s<br><br>\`\`\` |\\n\\n## 🛬 Post-Flight Phase\\n\\n| Step | staging | production |\\n|------|---------|---------|\\n| [ ] Step 2: Verify Health Checks 🛬👤<br><em>👤 PIC: ops-team@example.com · 👥 Reviewer: qa-team@example.com</em><br>📎 <em>Evidence Required: command_output, screenshot</em> | Check application health endpoints:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>curl https://app-\${NAMESPACE}.example.com/health<br>\`\`\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC · [ ] Reviewer<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**command_output**:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>{<br>  \\"status\\": \\"healthy\\",<br>  \\"version\\": \\"1.0.0\\",<br>  \\"environment\\": \\"staging\\"<br>}<br><br>\`\`\` | Check application health endpoints:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>curl https://app-\${NAMESPACE}.example.com/health<br>\`\`\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC · [ ] Reviewer<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**command_output**:<br>\`\`\`bash<br>{<br>  \\"status\\": \\"healthy\\",<br>  \\"version\\": \\"1.0.0\\",<br>  \\"environment\\": \\"production\\"<br>}<br><br>\`\`\`<br><br>**screenshot**: Health check dashboard<br>![Evidence](./evidence/prod-health-dashboard.png) |\\n| [ ] Step 3: Monitor Error Rates 🛬👤<br><em>👤 PIC: sre-team@example.com</em><br>📎 <em>Evidence Required: screenshot</em> | Monitor error rates for 15 minutes<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**screenshot**: Error rate below 0.1% in staging<br>![Evidence](./evidence/staging-metrics.png) | Monitor error rates for 15 minutes<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC<br><br>**Captured Evidence:**<br><br>**screenshot**: Error rate below 0.05% in production<br>![Evidence](./evidence/prod-metrics.png) |\\n| [ ] Step 4: No Reviewer Step 🛬⚙️<br><em>👤 PIC: ops-team@example.com</em><br>📎 <em>Evidence Optional: command_output</em> | \`kubectl get pods -n \${NAMESPACE}\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC | \`kubectl get pods -n \${NAMESPACE}\`<br><br>**Sign-off:** [ ] PIC |\\n\\n"
`;

exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: nestedSubSteps3Levels — compact single-env with deep nesting 1`] = `
"# Nested Sub-Steps (3 Levels) — Production\\n\\n## Step 1: Complex Deployment\\n\\n_Multi-tier application deployment_\\n\\n> PIC: DevOps Team · Timeline: 2024-01-15 10:00\\n\\n- [ ] **1.1 Database Tier**\\n  > PIC: DBA Team\\n\\n  Deploy database components\\n\\n  - [ ] **1.1.1 Deploy PostgreSQL**\\n    \`\`\`bash\\n    helm install postgres bitnami/postgresql\\n    \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.1.1 Create Database Schema**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      psql -f schema.sql\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.1.2 Load Initial Data**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      psql -f seed-data.sql\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.1.3 Verify Database Connection**\\n      Test connection from app pod\\n\\n  - [ ] **1.1.2 Deploy Redis Cache**\\n    \`\`\`bash\\n    helm install redis bitnami/redis\\n    \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.2.1 Configure Redis Cluster**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      redis-cli cluster init\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.2.2 Verify Redis Connection**\\n      Test Redis connectivity\\n\\n- [ ] **1.2 Application Tier**\\n  > PIC: Backend Team\\n\\n  Deploy application services\\n\\n  - [ ] **1.2.1 Deploy API Service**\\n    \`\`\`bash\\n    kubectl apply -f api-service.yaml\\n    \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.2.1.1 Wait for API Pods**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      kubectl wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app=api\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.2.1.2 Run API Health Check**\\n      Verify /health endpoint returns 200\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.2.1.3 Run Integration Tests**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      npm run test:integration\\n      \`\`\`\\n"
`;

exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: nestedSubSteps4Levels — compact single-env with 4 levels of nesting 1`] = `
"# Nested Sub-Steps (4 Levels) — Production\\n\\n## Step 1: Full Stack Deployment\\n\\n_Complete application stack with all dependencies_\\n\\n- [ ] **1.1 Infrastructure Layer**\\n  Setup infrastructure components\\n\\n  - [ ] **1.1.1 Network Configuration**\\n    \`\`\`bash\\n    terraform apply -target=module.networking\\n    \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.1.1 Create VPC**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      aws ec2 create-vpc --cidr-block 10.0.0.0/16\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.1.1.1 Tag VPC Resources**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws ec2 create-tags --resources \${VPC_ID} --tags Key=Environment,Value=\${ENV}\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.1.1.2 Enable DNS Hostnames**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws ec2 modify-vpc-attribute --vpc-id \${VPC_ID} --enable-dns-hostnames\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.1.2 Configure Security Groups**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      aws ec2 create-security-group --group-name app-sg\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.1.2.1 Add Ingress Rules**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress --group-id \${SG_ID} --protocol tcp --port 443\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.1.2.2 Add Egress Rules**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws ec2 authorize-security-group-egress --group-id \${SG_ID} --protocol -1\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n  - [ ] **1.1.2 Load Balancer Setup**\\n    \`\`\`bash\\n    aws elbv2 create-load-balancer --name app-lb\\n    \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.2.1 Configure Target Groups**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      aws elbv2 create-target-group --name app-targets\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.2.1.1 Register Targets**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws elbv2 register-targets --target-group-arn \${TG_ARN}\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n        - [ ] **1.1.2.1.1.1 Configure Health Checks**\\n          \`\`\`bash\\n          aws elbv2 modify-target-group --target-group-arn \${TG_ARN} --health-check-path /health\\n          \`\`\`\\n\\n    - [ ] **1.1.2.2 Add Listeners**\\n      \`\`\`bash\\n      aws elbv2 create-listener --load-balancer-arn \${LB_ARN}\\n      \`\`\`\\n\\n      - [ ] **1.1.2.2.1 Configure SSL Certificate**\\n        \`\`\`bash\\n        aws elbv2 add-listener-certificates --listener-arn \${LISTENER_ARN}\\n        \`\`\`\\n\\n        - [ ] **1.1.2.2.1.1 Verify SSL Configuration**\\n          Test HTTPS endpoint with curl -v\\n"
`;

exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: parentStepWithSubstepsAndRollback — compact single-env with rollback 1`] = `
"# Test Parent Step Rollback — Production\\n\\n## Step 1: Stage 1 (1% Traffic)\\n\\n_Migrate 1% traffic (weight=10, legacy weight=990)_\\n\\n- [ ] **1.1 Update Configuration**\\n  Update the application configuration\\n\\n  \`\`\`bash\\n  kubectl apply -f config.yaml\\n  \`\`\`\\n\\n- [ ] **1.2 Deploy Pods**\\n  Deploy the application pods\\n\\n  \`\`\`bash\\n  kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml\\n  \`\`\`\\n\\n- [ ] **1.3 Verify Deployment**\\n  Verify all pods are running\\n\\n  \`\`\`bash\\n  kubectl get pods -n \${NAMESPACE}\\n  \`\`\`\\n\\n- [ ] **🔄 Rollback**\\n  Rollback to previous deployment version\\n\\n  \`\`\`bash\\n  kubectl rollout undo deployment/app -n \${NAMESPACE}\\n  kubectl wait --for=condition=available deployment/app -n \${NAMESPACE}\\n  \`\`\`\\n"
`;

exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: reviewerAndEnvEvidence — compact single-env with PIC/Reviewer/evidence 1`] = `
"# Reviewer and Environment-Specific Evidence Test — Production\\n\\n## Step 1: Deploy Application\\n\\n> PIC: ops-team@example.com · Reviewer: sre-lead@example.com\\n\\nDeploy the application to Kubernetes:\\n\`\`\`bash\\nkubectl apply -f deployment.yaml -n \${NAMESPACE}\\nkubectl scale deployment/app --replicas=\${REPLICAS}\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n\\n**screenshot**: Production dashboard showing 5 healthy pods\\n\\n![Evidence](./evidence/prod-dashboard.png)\\n\\n**command_output**: Production deployment output showing 5 pods\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\ndeployment.apps/app created\\ndeployment.apps/app scaled\\nNAME      READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\\napp-0     1/1     Running   0          15s\\napp-1     1/1     Running   0          15s\\napp-2     1/1     Running   0          15s\\napp-3     1/1     Running   0          15s\\napp-4     1/1     Running   0          15s\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 2: Verify Health Checks\\n\\n> PIC: ops-team@example.com · Reviewer: qa-team@example.com\\n\\nCheck application health endpoints:\\n\`\`\`bash\\ncurl https://app-\${NAMESPACE}.example.com/health\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n\\n**command_output**\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\n{\\n  \\"status\\": \\"healthy\\",\\n  \\"version\\": \\"1.0.0\\",\\n  \\"environment\\": \\"production\\"\\n}\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n**screenshot**: Health check dashboard\\n\\n![Evidence](./evidence/prod-health-dashboard.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 3: Monitor Error Rates\\n\\n> PIC: sre-team@example.com\\n\\nMonitor error rates for 15 minutes\\n\\n**screenshot**: Error rate below 0.05% in production\\n\\n![Evidence](./evidence/prod-metrics.png)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 4: No Reviewer Step\\n\\n> PIC: ops-team@example.com\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\nkubectl get pods -n \${NAMESPACE}\\n\`\`\`\\n"
`;

exports[`Compact Markdown manual format (--compact) > snapshot: withCaptureExpect — compact single-env with capture/expect 1`] = `
"# Capture and Expect Test — Staging\\n\\n## Step 1: Build image\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\ndocker build -t myapp .\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 2: Check pod count\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\nkubectl get pods -n prod | grep -c Running\\n\`\`\`\\n\\nExpected:\\n- [ ] at least 1 line(s)\\n- [ ] value ≥ 3\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 3: Deploy\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\nkubectl set image deployment/myapp myapp=myapp:latest\\n\`\`\`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 4: Verify image\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\nkubectl get pod -l app=myapp -o jsonpath='{.items[0].spec.containers[0].imageID}'\\n\`\`\`\\n\\nExpected:\\n- [ ] contains: \${IMAGE_ID}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 5: Health check\\n\\n\`\`\`bash\\ncurl -s https://staging.example.com/health | jq .status\\n\`\`\`\\n\\nExpected:\\n- [ ] equals \\"healthy\\"\\n"
`;
